#!/usr/bin/env bash

cat << 'EOF'
Hooks deny these calls: `WebFetch` of any github.com URL, `curl https://github.com/...` (and wget), `gh api repos/<owner>/<repo>/contents/...` reads.
- Prefer a clone over fetching repository files: read the clone directly, `git show <ref>:<path>` for a file at a ref.
- Prefer `gh pr view <n> --repo <owner>/<repo> --comments` and `gh pr diff <n>` over fetching the PR page; likewise `gh issue view <n> --comments`, `gh release view <tag>`, `gh run view <id> --log-failed`.
- Prefer `gh search <code|issues|prs|repos> <query>` over fetching github.com/search.
- Prefer `gh api <path>` over fetching api.github.com (anonymous: 60 requests/hour).
EOF
